oid readObject(ObjectInputStream in) throws IOException, ClassNotFoundException {\r\n    readBaseObject(in);\r\n    defaultAutoCommit = in.readBoolean();\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1777643978594}}
[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_dQBUaEzQoUvjfyvpGBHiSaqx|fc_0c076d5c05a098960169f4b1ca362c81a3becb67955f8a04fc", "toolName": "read", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "/*\r\n * Copyright (c) 2004, PostgreSQL Global Development Group\r\n * See the LICENSE file in the project root for more information.\r\n */\r\n\r\npackage org.postgresql.ds;\r\n\r\nimport org.postgresql.ds.common.BaseDataSource;\r\n\r\nimport java.io.IOException;\r\nimport java.io.ObjectInputStream;\r\nimport java.io.ObjectOutputStream;\r\nimport java.io.Serializable;\r\nimport java.sql.SQLException;\r\n\r\nimport javax.sql.ConnectionPoolDataSource;\r\nimport javax.sql.PooledConnection;\r\n\r\n/**\r\n * PostgreSQL implementation of ConnectionPoolDataSource. The app server or middleware vendor should\r\n * provide a DataSource implementation that takes advantage of this ConnectionPoolDataSource. If\r\n * not, you can use the PostgreSQL implementation known as PoolingDataSource, but that should only\r\n * be used if your server or middleware vendor does not provide their own. Why? The server may want\r\n * to reuse the same Connection across all EJBs requesting a Connection within the same Transaction,\r\n * or provide other similar advanced features.\r\n *\r\n * <p>\r\n * In any case, in order to use this ConnectionPoolDataSource, you must set the property\r\n * databaseName. The settings for serverName, portNumber, user, and password are optional. Note:\r\n * these properties are declared in the superclass.\r\n * </p>\r\n *\r\n * <p>\r\n * This implementation supports JDK 1.3 and higher.\r\n * </p>\r\n *\r\n * @author Aaron Mulder (ammulder@chariotsolutions.com)\r\n */\r\npublic class PGConnectionPoolDataSource extends BaseDataSource\r\n    implements ConnectionPoolDataSource, Serializable {\r\n  private boolean defaultAutoCommit = true;\r\n\r\n  /**\r\n   * Gets a description of this DataSource.\r\n   */\r\n  public String getDescription() {\r\n    return \"ConnectionPoolDataSource from \" + org.postgresql.util.DriverInfo.DRIVER_FULL_NAME;\r\n  }\r\n\r\n  /**\r\n   * Gets a connection which may be pooled by the app server or middleware implementation of\r\n   * DataSource.\r\n   *\r\n   * @throws java.sql.SQLException Occurs when the physical database connection cannot be\r\n   *         established.\r\n   */\r\n  public PooledConnection getPooledConnection() throws SQLException {\r\n    return new PGPooledConnection(getConnection(), defaultAutoCommit);\r\n  }\r\n\r\n  /**\r\n   * Gets a connection which may be pooled by the app server or middleware implementation of\r\n   * DataSource.\r\n   *\r\n   * @throws java.sql.SQLException Occurs when the physical database connection cannot be\r\n   *         established.\r\n   */\r\n  public PooledConnection getPooledConnection(String user, String password) throws SQLException {\r\n    return new PGPooledConnection(getConnection(user, password), defaultAutoCommit);\r\n  }\r\n\r\n  /**\r\n   * Gets whether connections supplied by this pool will have autoCommit turned on by default. The\r\n   * default value is <tt>false</tt>, so that autoCommit will be turned off by default.\r\n   *\r\n   * @return true if connections supplied by this pool will have autoCommit\r\n   */\r\n  public boolean isDefaultAutoCommit() {\r\n    return defaultAutoCommit;\r\n  }\r\n\r\n  /**\r\n   * Sets whether connections supplied by this pool will have autoCommit turned on by default. The\r\n   * default value is <tt>false</tt>, so that autoCommit will be turned off by default.\r\n   *\r\n   * @param defaultAutoCommit whether connections supplied by this pool will have autoCommit\r\n   */\r\n  public void setDefaultAutoCommit(boolean defaultAutoCommit) {\r\n    this.defaultAutoCommit = defaultAutoCommit;\r\n  }\r\n\r\n  private void writeObject(ObjectOutputStream out) throws IOException {\r\n    writeBaseObject(out);\r\n    out.writeBoolean(defaultAutoCommit);\r\n  }\r\n\r\n  private void readObject(ObjectInputStream in) throws IOException, ClassNotFoundException {\r\n    readBaseObject(in);\r\n    defaultAutoCommit = in.readBoolean();\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1777643978594}}
[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering Docker setup**\n\nI'm thinking about whether to reuse a shared utility to start Docker. However, the \"active class only\" concept might require me to include setup details. I want to be careful to avoid duplicating the database if I go that route. It's a bit tricky trying to balance these ideas without running into issues. I'll need to clarify what best approach to take for the setup while keeping everything efficient.\n\n**Exploring database testing**\n\nI'm considering the utility of database tests, especially with Docker. There’s a potential conflict if multiple test classes start Docker on the same port, like with Opengauss_jdbcTest. It could be safer to use different host ports or ensure tests run sequentially with Gradle. The internal Docker port is 5432, and I should use 15433 to avoid conflicts. I might explore using mocks instead of starting a DB, but that could shift the tests toward integration. I'll need to check the PGConnectionPoolDataSource API next.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0c076d5c05a098960169f4b1bdfa5481a3addeba8d045695f4\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp9LHKf6J-Sl7OIQdyUTxQqkzCKqZVRWBaP-fZS8nnMaX7RE8i8YP3ZX2QAGAcLO0J6F2JfMwvw3TYA-giBYjo7XnRRLyoWOkdZnFHmtxG9b6iE7cY5aR3uoBwKPu89XPab1aLlqs-D43pwErCzjNjpN8LqJICBM2umemsBEHvcmMZ_o2uSy1TH9HUSPMv5vtm1ymzsVsGneyoY6epkUVVwV12DEzCndlKXVPY11z0TRfn4X2yjYUibowzg7FugWcK4K3pa8Moulsg7REXULlwUJOZpzHkQLB3axTG2cPkvArMLFAPv9Y485GVRNGkSJhooCF7COyNpLc8y7hfyKVpj7l3UvJmN988K_RS6TxD48MxkJF6X1sa3pnHsCKfmxCYGvfspQh5fJY_q1Pz4jl79kidRzfYMCbqM-bE357EKTLrf_LhX0fXJVSIf63qEe87KR_89zQjqJ_EZuy2SFqAxKkJUymptDpMBGWma9rpyoY3l4W3rKAcX46Hiw8zf8jlO_rDnZ8X4IvtdMgRJde98-FIh5yrTSSAmQepndIv0XTCTMDcWZfIbHhpbQh2beNbJEyexzFwCqhh1WvnXgVj2GQSmJkz_ilaZx-c6NNOjzrMUoeLWx7VKvrvvOFFU7ZxmvK9EhQfS4WU8PlrH-AbsPf-O3ylo7zCYl-GcKw88-NPHmGSaA82LrrwIJjVqYXcLnUFPm16_8jiXy2nG_WKI_E3P15ePnCSqDMjE-79CCmuQXJLt